{
  "texts": [
    "People with dementia (PwD) participating in our study were aged 58-88 years whereas supporters were aged 32-70 years.",
    "As these ranges suggest, supporters were significantly younger than PwD (independent samples t-test, t = 5.059, p < 0.0001).",
    "Whereas gender roles were equally distributed for PwD (7 women, 7 men, 1 of nonbinary gender), supporters were predominantly female (11 women, 2 men).",
    "To compare the distribution of genders across the two groups, we used a two-sided Fisher's exact test which works on 2x2 contingency tables.",
    "The chi-squared test allows for larger tables but requires a larger sample size (Hazra and Gogtay, 2016; Sundjaja et al., 2024)."
  ]
}